Cook fusilli according to package directions. Drain and rinse under cold water; transfer to a large bowl. Meanwhile, halve the cucumber lengthwise and use the end of a spoon to scoop and discard seeds. Chop cucumber into 1/2-inch (1 cm) pieces; set aside. Lemony-Yogurt Dressing: Whisk together yogurt, mayonnaise, olive oil, lemon juice and zest, garlic, salt and pepper. Add cucumber, chickpeas, onion and orange pepper to pasta; toss with dressing. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or up to 4 hours. Fold in olives and mint just before serving.